&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited for the above posts in Emergency Medicine based at James Cook University Hospital starting as soon as possible for 8 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post duties include initial management of emergency cases presenting to the A &amp; E Department, conducting minor operations &amp; procedures when indicated and supervision of the discharge of patients home. The successful candidate will take part in a full shift rota with the existing staff to provide 24 hour on site CT1 cover for the department attracting an on call supplement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must have completed at least 2 years hospital based medical experience at Foundation level or equivalent and have the appropriate competencies or equivalent experience. Full GMC Registration is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
